{"section":15,"text":"So that's a positive flow sign, indicating that the mass is connected to the thyroid.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.047089,0.086766,0.093809,0.09848,0.096781,0.095412,0.093083,0.0872,0.088186,0.078544,0.068352,0.066298],"unified_progress":[0.057429,0.075686,0.092333,0.10214,0.10502,0.099894,0.096711,0.089814,0.086609,0.073684,0.063266,0.057409]},{"section":16,"text":"But the history of it resolving before at age 3.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.04262,0.082085,0.08783,0.090553,0.094184,0.10003,0.094926,0.093767,0.088933,0.08624,0.076012,0.062821],"unified_progress":[0.090478,0.10588,0.094853,0.089862,0.088925,0.087391,0.084622,0.087317,0.079046,0.074083,0.06467,0.052875]},{"section":17,"text":"At that age, maybe it was a thyroglossal duct cyst?","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041831,0.079478,0.087193,0.09354,0.096638,0.10061,0.097209,0.093275,0.093318,0.083304,0.071757,0.061846],"unified_progress":[0.069832,0.093572,0.10043,0.10089,0.097746,0.097839,0.090499,0.088198,0.083234,0.070732,0.058771,0.048256]},{"section":18,"text":"Because thyroglossal duct cysts are midline, can fluctuate, and often present in children.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032492,0.06899,0.082984,0.095599,0.10298,0.10513,0.10506,0.096922,0.090138,0.087011,0.070871,0.061821],"unified_progress":[0.040298,0.066745,0.093699,0.099362,0.10242,0.11457,0.10322,0.096497,0.090147,0.080692,0.063566,0.048779]},{"section":19,"text":"They can get infected, which would explain the pain, redness, and needing antibiotics.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033188,0.069843,0.078905,0.086596,0.094172,0.099988,0.10249,0.099888,0.094625,0.089702,0.08144,0.069158],"unified_progress":[0.041507,0.062743,0.0736,0.081463,0.090128,0.10145,0.098012,0.099242,0.098978,0.09617,0.087992,0.068717]},{"section":20,"text":"But after the infection resolves, the cyst might reduce in size but not completely go away.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.04063,0.077459,0.081943,0.086358,0.09127,0.096127,0.097209,0.09618,0.09266,0.087719,0.079976,0.072469],"unified_progress":[0.051615,0.067476,0.075747,0.081835,0.088587,0.094386,0.094937,0.096619,0.095752,0.09313,0.08606,0.073856]},{"section":21,"text":"Also, thyroglossal duct cysts typically move with tongue protrusion because they are attached to the hyoid bone via the thyroglossal duct.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036662,0.075698,0.086221,0.094318,0.096927,0.099248,0.098814,0.092907,0.096105,0.083406,0.073117,0.066578],"unified_progress":[0.041786,0.067415,0.087143,0.097008,0.10215,0.10373,0.10037,0.095273,0.095662,0.081528,0.069148,0.058782]},{"section":22,"text":"So the flow sign is positive here, which supports that.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034564,0.072085,0.087209,0.093585,0.095115,0.093423,0.094625,0.091328,0.090282,0.087911,0.080463,0.079412],"unified_progress":[0.064349,0.06745,0.077817,0.086873,0.090872,0.090441,0.091543,0.091429,0.089563,0.087774,0.083072,0.078817]},{"section":23,"text":"Another possibility could be a branchial cleft cyst, but those are usually lateral, not midline.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029611,0.065407,0.079495,0.089323,0.095487,0.098736,0.10138,0.099799,0.098494,0.092902,0.082772,0.066597],"unified_progress":[0.035677,0.064597,0.083902,0.095037,0.1,0.10135,0.10139,0.099565,0.096918,0.091714,0.074802,0.055047]},{"section":24,"text":"A lymph node mass?","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027472,0.065165,0.080669,0.09018,0.095897,0.099217,0.1018,0.10037,0.10067,0.092647,0.082359,0.063543],"unified_progress":[0.039505,0.068696,0.086401,0.097509,0.10285,0.10189,0.10211,0.099133,0.09592,0.087642,0.069729,0.048619]},{"section":25,"text":"But lymph nodes are more likely to be tender and might have other signs of infection.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.020663,0.053472,0.069476,0.080908,0.089979,0.09658,0.10598,0.10838,0.10734,0.10364,0.095709,0.067873],"unified_progress":[0.032022,0.057918,0.074244,0.083133,0.095581,0.098313,0.10176,0.10737,0.10528,0.10704,0.084525,0.052813]},{"section":26,"text":"Since the antibiotics didn't resolve the mass, it's probably not an abscess.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029699,0.062947,0.074093,0.08218,0.088032,0.093677,0.099584,0.10157,0.10202,0.098913,0.091677,0.07561],"unified_progress":[0.039626,0.062596,0.074525,0.082641,0.091098,0.094242,0.098339,0.10118,0.10132,0.10156,0.087702,0.065166]},{"section":27,"text":"The fact that it recurred and the prior episode that resolved spontaneously also points more towards a congenital anomaly like a thyroglossal duct cyst.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032363,0.066638,0.077107,0.084784,0.089947,0.095199,0.096455,0.095725,0.09834,0.093234,0.086863,0.083344],"unified_progress":[0.046645,0.070252,0.079027,0.086631,0.090539,0.093937,0.094036,0.094107,0.094836,0.088865,0.083725,0.0774]},{"section":28,"text":"Thyroid adenoma or goiter?","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025343,0.060159,0.076336,0.087139,0.095084,0.098637,0.1017,0.10017,0.10027,0.094697,0.086174,0.074293],"unified_progress":[0.043039,0.066286,0.083614,0.094275,0.097327,0.099565,0.099412,0.096356,0.093779,0.087068,0.075879,0.0634]},{"section":29,"text":"A goiter would be more diffuse enlargement, but a cyst could be a colloid nodule.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026775,0.062328,0.077104,0.088276,0.095542,0.10003,0.10326,0.10085,0.099602,0.093651,0.083274,0.069298],"unified_progress":[0.039988,0.064366,0.082685,0.093357,0.099886,0.10281,0.10139,0.099399,0.096095,0.089207,0.073939,0.05688]},{"section":30,"text":"However, the movement with tongue protrusion is classic for thyroglossal duct cyst.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028632,0.063715,0.076744,0.086751,0.092996,0.097714,0.099999,0.097155,0.099202,0.092206,0.08547,0.079416],"unified_progress":[0.038503,0.061845,0.079209,0.090464,0.097056,0.10222,0.099467,0.097354,0.096959,0.087843,0.079517,0.069565]},{"section":31,"text":"Also, they can become infected, which would explain the prior episodes.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023338,0.055011,0.069593,0.081353,0.091787,0.099003,0.10468,0.10398,0.10229,0.098304,0.092809,0.077855],"unified_progress":[0.057189,0.058947,0.068261,0.075964,0.085773,0.093235,0.095303,0.09942,0.099719,0.10004,0.092071,0.074078]},{"section":32,"text":"Since it's midline, persistent after infection, and moves with tongue, thyroglossal duct cyst is the most likely diagnosis here.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02605,0.057048,0.069136,0.077483,0.083446,0.089064,0.093377,0.094406,0.099587,0.097466,0.098175,0.11476],"unified_progress":[0.030735,0.051467,0.063809,0.073328,0.079213,0.08721,0.089072,0.094038,0.10017,0.10018,0.10955,0.12123]}]}}